perl-WWW-Babelfish
-------------------------------------------
This module is a simple perl front-end to the Babelfish translation
server.  It makes an attempt at breaking longer pieces of text up into 
chunks that Babelfish can handle and then reassembling them. This 
version also contains preliminary support for the Google translation 
engine.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.19-4
  perl-5.8.7-5
  perl-HTML-Parser-3.37-2
  perl-IO-String-1.05-2
  perl-libwww-perl-5.801-2

Canonical homepage:
  http://search.cpan.org/~durist/WWW-Babelfish/

Canonical download:
  http://www.cpan.org/authors/id/D/DU/DURIST/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack perl-WWW-Babelfish-0.15-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./perl-WWW-Babelfish-0.15-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/perl-WWW-Babelfish-0.15-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/perl-WWW-Babelfish-0.15-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /etc/postinstall/perl-WWW-Babelfish.sh
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.8/WWW/Babelfish.pm
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.8/auto/WWW/Babelfish/autosplit.ix
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.8/cygwin/auto/WWW/Babelfish/.packlist
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/perl-WWW-Babelfish-0.15.README
  /usr/share/doc/perl-WWW-Babelfish-0.15/Changes
  /usr/share/doc/perl-WWW-Babelfish-0.15/README
  /usr/share/man/man3/WWW.Babelfish.3pm.gz
  /usr/share/perl/cygwin-pods/5.8/WWW-Babelfish.pod

